# ARIA — Intake Form

> Step 1 of 7 modules. The structured entry point for every AI initiative in the ARIA platform.

## Files

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `aria-intake-form.jsx` | Full React component — all 7 steps, live ROI calculators, sample data pre-filled |
| `index.html` | GitHub Pages wrapper — drop both files in the same folder and open |

## Stack

- React 18 (no build step required via Babel standalone)
- Zero dependencies beyond React
- Works as a static file — no server needed

## Running locally

```bash
# Option 1 — open directly in browser (Chrome/Edge)
open index.html

# Option 2 — serve locally
npx serve .
# or
python3 -m http.server 3000
```

## Deploying to GitHub Pages

1. Push both files to your repo under `src/intake/`
2. Enable GitHub Pages from **Settings → Pages → Deploy from branch**
3. Set source to `main` and folder to `/src/intake`
4. Your form will be live at `https://[org].github.io/aria/`

## Sample data

The form ships with a pre-filled use case: **AI-Powered Trade Reconciliation Assistant** — a realistic Capital Group operations scenario covering all 7 steps including financials, KPIs, risk, and team allocation. Clear the fields to use as a blank intake form.

## What's collected

| Step | Section |
|---|---|
| 1 | Basic information — initiative name, auto-assigned use case ID, business line, team, sponsor, owner, dates, AI vendor |
| 2 | Problem statement — problem description, adoption headcount, urgency, cost of inaction, problem type |
| 3 | Strategic alignment — pillars, roadmap status, dependencies |
| 4 | Investment & return — total cost breakdown, return type, live ROI calculator, auto-calculated annual value and payback period |
| 5 | KPIs & success metrics — quantitative KPIs with baseline/target, qualitative 90-day and 12-month outcomes |
| 6 | Risk & compliance — data classification, client data exposure, regulatory scope, model risk, legal review |
| 7 | Team & resources — role assignments, allocation %, constraints, submission summary |

